    <h1 class="page-title">APRIL 21, 2020 MESSAGE FROM SUPERINTENDENT BRATTEN</h1>


    <div style="position: relative; padding-bottom: 75%; height: 0;"><iframe src="https://www.loom.com/embed/692fa0213d0e41febddf97e956e7d18c" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;"></iframe></div>


    <p dir="ltr"> </p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf">Good evening, I hope that you and your family are well!</b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf"> </b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf">As I’m sure that you have heard by now, Governor DeWine has ordered the schools closed for the remainder of this spring with no decisions being made at this time in regards to opening in the fall. Obviously, this is very disappointing for all of our staff and students, but the Governor felt that it just wasn’t safe to reopen at this time. With this closure also comes the cancellation of athletics, plays, the arts programs, and all of the other items that were planned this spring. I know we are all disappointed and all of us want to return to normalcy and get back to life as we know it as soon as possible. </b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf"> </b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf">I know that many students, staff, community members and parents have been struggling greatly with the change and because of these announcements and with the announcement yesterday we will have more people struggling and I urge you that we all need to be here for one another. If you know of someone struggling, please reach out for help and if you do not know where to turn please feel free to give us a call so that we can help to point you in the right direction. We cannot let this thing beat any of us.<br><br>
We don’t have many answers right now and believe me when I say we are frustrated as well.  Since we do not have answers regarding the future right now, we will begin work immediately on different options for next school year based on the orders that we will finally receive in a several weeks from now. We will work on various scenarios and try to plan for whatever decisions are made that we will be expected to follow.</b></p>

<p dir="ltr"> </p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf">Currently, we are keeping our graduation date options open and as previously announced continue to hold various scenarios open for our Seniors at various sites.  We are hoping that those options will not go away with time and that we are able to honor our seniors as best as we can under the circumstances.<br><br>
I wanted to remind you that we are still serving lunches to ALL SMF FAMILIES Monday through Friday at Echo Hills,  Lakeview, Kimpton and the High School from 8a-10a, and we still have our tech support people at SMFHS on Tuesdays and Thursdays from 9a-11a at the Commons doors entrance, should you need to pick up or exchange technology for your students. We are also now serving the meals on Monday evening only at Lakeview from 4pm to 6pm for those that cannot make the other times. We had over 45 families take advantage of this our first night so we are glad that we could fill that obvious need!</b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf">I want to thank everyone that is taking advantage of the food opportunities as we’ve nearly tripled our number of lunches we serve since the beginning!<br><br>
I do want to publicize one more thing this evening:</b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf">Friday afternoon we'd like to invite our elementary and Lakeview students to head to their bus stops at their usual drop off time to catch a glimpse of their favorite SMF drivers!  Buses will stop at every stop and open the bus doors to greet students.  Please consider walking your student to his or her stop and, while maintaining social distance at the stop, saying hello to your drivers.  For your health and safety, please respect the social distancing guidelines. Busses will not be transporting students or allowing access onto the bus.  We felt like this would be a nice pick-me-up that many of us need right now.</b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf"> </b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf">Also, Friday evening, we'd like to invite our High School seniors to join us to "#SpotlightSMFSeniors" on Friday at 7:20pm.  We are opening up the high school parking lot loop for seniors to drive through, see the stadium lights on in their honor, and wave to SMFHS staff members who will be standing along the loop to honor the Class Of 2020!  In order to abide by the Governor's order, students will not be allowed to stop or get out of their vehicles.  </b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf"> </b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf">During these difficult times, we will continue to look for creative ways to still bring us safely together.  We will be announcing more events in the very near future.  We realize the importance that school plays in the lives of students and their families and we are going to continue to try to highlight ways to keep us close.</b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf"> </b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf">I’d like to end this evening with a positive message. This isn’t anything that any one of us ever imagined would happen. For many, this has become the hardest time in your lives. I beg that you lean on one another and if you don’t have anyone to lean on, please lean on our district by reaching out. We do not want to let this disease get the best of any of us and need to do all we can to try to make sure that doesn’t happen.</b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf"> </b></p>

<p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-9a1f2254-7fff-d5fb-460d-d8383830b0bf">I want to thank our teachers, staff, students, and parents for all that you are doing under very trying circumstances. You have been flexible, understanding, supportive, compassionate, and quite honestly -- just amazing. There is not one part of this group that hasn’t been amazing in helping us to get through all of this and I can’t thank you more. We will get through this and I pray that you and your family stay safe and healthy. Until next week... Have a great night.  </b></p>

